# Tailwind CSS Conventions

## Dark Mode

- Strategy: `class` (toggle via className on `<html>`)
- Design primarily for dark theme — CARTO dark tiles set the tone

## Custom Theme Colors

Use the project-specific colors for pin types:

- `flood` — water/flood incidents
- `pothole` — road damage
- `passable` — passable but risky areas
- `robbery` — crime incidents

```tsx
<Badge className="bg-flood/20 text-flood">Alagamento</Badge>
<Badge className="bg-robbery/20 text-robbery">Assalto</Badge>
```

## Custom Animations

Available animations: `fadeIn`, `slideUp`, `pulse`, `float`, `shimmer`

```tsx
<div className="animate-fadeIn">...</div>
```

## Best Practices

- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes
- Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
- Use `@apply` sparingly — only in `index.css` for global base styles
- Use responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` for layout
- Use `tailwind-merge` (via `cn()`) to avoid class conflicts
- Keep spacing consistent: `p-4`, `gap-4`, `space-y-4`
